<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-08-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-08-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="29" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d29">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Ewing</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-08-24"><hi rend="italic">August 24,
                                1894</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Reported that Belgium prohibits landing American live cattle because of
                            danger from pleuro-pneumonia. Secretary of Agriculture authorizes
                            positive denial of that disease in the United States. As important
                            cargoes are afloat and under charter, you will ascertain facts of
                            alleged prohibition and make above denial if necessary.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Gresham.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>